Oft doth Shadowheart's mind turn to her lost love, from whose ashes flowers now bloom.

EditorData.logicalname: Romance with non-illithid avatar - karlach, dead

Text.Value: Though the orb yet burns within thy chest, she didst contain its hunger. Thy life is thine own once more.
In Thaniel's realm, under nature's watch, Halsin found his purpose.
I can think of vanishingly few who would make a monster of themselves to save the world.
But rest assured, thine allies have not seen the last of thee.
She defied her paranoid queen, freed her people's rebel prince, and found an ally along the way.
Thou declared them soulless.
Hence thy revelry in thy new form.

EditorData.logicalname: Chose to thrive because MF doesn't stand for mind flayer

Text.Value: Wyll hath ventured to Avernus with his love, and hath left his father ruling in his place until his return.

EditorData.logicalname: Avatar Wyll Grand Duke went to Avernus

Text.Value: Her partner came to visit them in time. Shadowheart was nervous to introduce a stranger to their newly reclaimed lives. But their joy was only elevated by her own.

EditorData.logicalname: Romance with non-illithid avatar, not karlach

Text.Value: The Blade still doth devote himself to the protection of the Sword Coast.
She gave her self as she knew it so her friends could keep their souls - and she gained a new life in the bargain.
Sleep, if thou canst. And if not, all the better. Thou must be ready - I may have need of thee.
Halsin doth now live in the earth that he so loved. His body ample food for plants and animals.
Sweet Karlach, her death was foretold, and yet what life was left was ripped from her before her time.
But she still hath her freedom, and with that she can do much. For the rest, she hath her resolve.
Thy wizard sacrificed himself to save the world.

EditorData.logicalname: Did not blow up with Gale

Text.Value: Thus, is thy story concluded. For now.
And she is not alone. Her illithid partner is by her side, and doth soothe her with its company.
Though he beareth the visage of a devil, he commandeth the respect of patriar and pauper alike.
Mizora no longer doth darken his doorstep. He relieth now on blade, bow, and wits.
And what more beautiful terror can there be than that wrought by Minthara and her love?
Thy infernal engine is sated, stilled by the illithid form that thou now callest thine own. Yet its power burns within thee still.
But, as ever, his hubris was his downfall. Gale failed to master the Crown's magic. It ignited the orb within him, and he perished in the blast.
The limits of thy power have not yet been reached, but to unlock thy whole potential requires time. Forbearance.
Lady Shar's right hand. She travelled for a while with her illithid love before returning to the Cloister.

EditorData.logicalname: Sacrificed parents, stayed on Shar path, illithid avatar stayed together

Text.Value: Fortunately, thy friends fare better than thee.

EditorData.NodeContext: addressing Dark Urge avatar, but 'friends' means other players
EditorData.logicalname: OTHER AV PRESENT + DIDNT MAKE RAPHAEL DEAL

Text.Value: Sleep, rest, revel. But be ready. For thou mayest yet be needed.
There she devoted herself once more to the cleansing of the ranks.
Thy soul is forfeit, but thy curiosity is not. Thou hast still much to discover, and if I know thee, thou wilt find thy rewards.
As Astarion's strength groweth, the likelihood of her cure - and their return to this plane - groweth too.
I once asked of thee - do illithids possess souls?
But the one thing she could not do for him was cure his greatest love.
Gale became a god as he once dreamed he would, and under his pantheon of ruthless ambition doth he draw new souls to his creed.
Idle lives do not make for happy heroes, nor doth time change them. Minsc doth reject the tedium of sedentary life, and adventureth yet in search of souls to save.
Thou art a true hero, and Mystra knows it. With thy sacrifice, she hath welcomed thee into Elysium.
Wyll.
Grand Duke though he may now be, every highsun, Wyll still maketh time to tend to more humble roots.
And though Astarion doth spend his days sleeping once more, he doth not sleep alone.
And she is not alone. Her illithid partner is by her side, and doth soothe her with its company.
His love is right beside him, in body, mind, and blade.
Thy part in this hath rendered divine consequence. For with his death did he finally earn fair Mystra's grace. Thou hast restored a wizard to his god.
But she is not alone. A rare find indeed that partner, who stands beside her now. Few have the fortitude for such a role, and no one else, her love.
Gale stayed with Karlach 'til the very end. His love for her never wavered, even as she passed.
Thou were wise to seek refuge from the quickening madness with thy death.
His only regret, that Karlach doth not fight beside him.

Synopsis: Scene that plays after END_GodsAndMonsters_WithersMeeting in which Withers settles the accounts of what happened to all the characters after the events of the game ended.
